Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 16:06:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] monitoring/ceph-mixin: bump pylint to 2.17.7 for Python 3.11+

pylint 2.6.0 pulls astroid 2.5 -> wrapt 1.12.1, whose decorators.py does
`from inspect import ... formatargspec`.  formatargspec was removed in
Python 3.11, so *importing* pylint (e.g. when `tox -e lint` runs it)
aborts on 3.11+ with:

  ImportError: cannot import name 'formatargspec' from 'inspect'

pip install itself succeeds; the failure is at import time, not at venv
setup.

pylint 2.17.7 (last 2.x) pulls wrapt 1.17.x, which is Python 3.11+
compatible, and avoids the checker renames pylint 3.x would force on
.pylintrc.  A few removed python3-* porting options in .pylintrc now
emit useless-option-value warnings but do not fail the run.

Scope: this restores pylint usability on 3.11/3.12.  On 3.13 the astroid
2.15 that 2.x pins still lacks PEP 695 `type` support, so fully clean
linting there would need pylint 3.x.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 monitoring/ceph-mixin/requirements-lint.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/monitoring/ceph-mixin/requirements-lint.txt b/monitoring/ceph-mixin/requirements-lint.txt
index 8c7219897..3c5b039f2 100644
--- a/monitoring/ceph-mixin/requirements-lint.txt
+++ b/monitoring/ceph-mixin/requirements-lint.txt
@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@ dataclasses==0.6
 types-dataclasses==0.6.1
 six==1.16.0
 toml==0.10.2
-pylint==2.6.0
+pylint==2.17.7
 isort==5.10.0
 mypy==0.910
 mypy-extensions==0.4.3
